House Resolution 541
By: Representative Burns of the 159th
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the legacy of the Battle of Brier Creek; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the Battle of Brier Creek, fought on March 3, 1779, in Screven County,
3 Georgia, was a pivotal conflict in the Southern Campaign of the American Revolutionary
4 War, where British forces under the command of Lieutenant Colonel Archibald Campbell
5 achieved a decisive victory over American forces led by General John Ashe; and
6 WHEREAS, this battle marked a significant moment in the conflict, as the British victory at
7 Brier Creek not only allowed them to maintain a foothold in Georgia but also paved the way
8 for their subsequent invasion of South Carolina, which was critical to the continuation of
9 British efforts to subdue the southern colonies; and
10 WHEREAS, the destruction of the bridge over Brier Creek by British forces, combined with
11 a surprise flanking maneuver, led to the swift defeat of American troops, resulting in a rout
12 and a major setback for the Patriot cause in Georgia and the Carolinas; and
13 WHEREAS, the Battle of Brier Creek is a vital yet often overlooked chapter in the history
14 of the American Revolution, contributing significantly to the broader understanding of the
