15 Southern Strategy employed by the British and the struggles faced by the Continental Army
16 during this phase of the war; and
17 WHEREAS, the Brier Creek Battlefield remains a historically significant site that is essential
18 for understanding the military strategies and challenges that shaped the outcome of the
19 American Revolution, particularly in the southern theater; and
20 WHEREAS, preserving the Brier Creek Battlefield provides an opportunity to educate future
21 generations about this crucial event in American history and honors the sacrifices made by
22 both American and British forces; and
23 WHEREAS, the preservation of the Brier Creek Battlefield will foster a greater appreciation
24 for the region's historical importance, contribute to local tourism, and support educational
25 initiatives focused on the American Revolution.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
27 the members of this body join in honoring the history and legacy of those who fought at the
28 Battle of Brier Creek, ensuring that their contributions to the struggle for American
29 independence are remembered and celebrated.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the
32 public and the press.
